  "label": "Griefcairn Peak",
  "description": "Griefcairn Peak rises above the shattered frontier of Anslem as a steep basalt massif scarred by old caldera fractures and long-run scree fans. Its upper ridgelines carry fields of vitrified slag and ash-glass shards, permanent evidence of the continent-scale catastrophe that reshaped Muraii’s highlands. A ring of ruined cairns and law-stones crowns the summit shelf, their chisel-cut clauses weathered but still legible in the thin, abrasive wind. Narrow goat-tracks thread the lower buttresses, marking the only reliable approach through unstable gullies and frequent rockfall.",
